snippet.textDisplay: Last week at valentines, a non-binary wrote me a very sweet letter. I wrote them back, but sadly it did not get processed by the delivering committee and is lost. Nevertheless, we chat and chat the following weekend, and I thought I found the right person. They is aware of priorities, and a very hard worker, both very attractive qualities, and as the days progress I feel like I'm falling deeper and deeper in love. We want to become comfortable friends first before our first date because we don't really know eachother much, and I want us to develop into something special. Come to think of it, we're opposites of one another; they is very outspoken, listens to rock, gothic, has many friends... meanwhile, I'm quiet, only few I could call true friends, and listens to these type of calming music. I'd like to believe that we're opposites attract, and we do have something in common: Love for science. I really, really want to get to know them better, but I'm not the best approacher and frankly speaking, they always seem preoccupied; their friends, locking in, so on so forth... well, I could do the latter too but I'm done with all my papers, and sometimes I think I should have postponed so that I could hang out with them months before the valentine. The moments we do talk in real life, they don't return eye contact, and sometimes I feel like they ignore my messages. I don't wanna be controlling, I'm no control freak, though I would be lying if I say it doesn't hurt. They is so smart, I really would want this to work, but I'm scared that they may lose feelings... it's only been a couple days since valentines, yet I can't help but overthink. It's too early to say, but I'm in love with them. I just know I am, am I weird for this?
